      free
     </sub>
     of 0.218/0.275 (
     <a>
      <span>
       Table 1
      </span>
     </a>
     ).
    </p>
    <p>
     The quaternary complex structure shows that Shq1 exclusively contacts Cbf5 at the PUA domain, the C-terminal extension (CTE) and a small part of the catalytic domain (
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      Figures 3A
     </xref>
     and
     <xref ref-type="fig">
      None
     </xref>
     ). The Shq1–Cbf5 complex buries 1803 Å
     <sup>
      2
     </sup>
     of solvent accessible area in Cbf5, with 612 Å
     <sup>
      2
     </sup>
     contributed by the PUA domain, 1082 Å
     <sup>
      2
